  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted spanning all five flow-speed operating points; parameter sweeps across impeller clearance, volute geometry, and inlet angle confirmed that the RH index ranking is stable across the design space. Sensitivity findings are discussed in the validation report VR-CPB-2024-07 and summarised in the decision record.",
